# Metrics (all required)

1. MPJAE: |pred - true|.mean() over all muscles and frames
2. Per-muscle R2: sklearn r2_score for each of 80 muscles (report top-10, bottom-10)
3. Per-muscle mean bias: pred.mean(0) - true.mean(0) (positive=over-activates)
4. Per-muscle Pearson correlation: scipy.stats.pearsonr per muscle
5. Temporal smoothness: |a[t+1]-a[t]|.mean() on predictions
6. Length MAE: |predicted_T - true_T|.mean() in frames

## Output
- Save all to results/{split}_metrics.json
- Print sorted per-muscle R2 table to stdout
- Log scalars + per-muscle R2 bar chart to W&B if run active
